    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="385"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d385">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_HHL1">Hopkins</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The President’s Special Assistant</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_HHL1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hopkins</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Director of War Mobilization</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="#p_BJF1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Byrnes</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d385fn1">Sent to Washington via military
                        channels, and forwarded by the White House Map Room to <persName
                            corresp="#p_BJF1">Byrnes</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-28">November 28,
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Extensive studies of various problems required before decision can be
                        reached.<note n="2" xml:id="d385fn2">See <persName corresp="#p_BJF1"
                            >Byrnes</persName>’ telegrams of November 24 and 27, 1943, <ref
                            target="#pg_395">pp. 395</ref> and <ref target="#pg_444">444</ref>,
                        respectively.</note> In meantime you should proceed as before the question
                    of increase in landing craft was raised.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
